        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 16 at 6:23PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 622 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles south of Easley, or 5 miles southwest of Powdersville, moving
southwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Easley, Piedmont, Norris, Powdersville, and Liberty.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
